            h2 A Matter of Contracts?
            img.croppedPhoto(src='../site/img/levineGrimmie.jpg' alt='levineGrimmie' align='right' style='width: 280px; height: auto')
            p.textwrap Adam Levine, who coached Christina during her competition in "The Voice", expressed his intentions to sign Grimmie on with "222 Records" and sign a record deal.  Fans of Grimmie wondered why she didn't outright sign on post-"The Voice".  According to "Sawdah" from "The Real Grimmie Blog", having to sign various contracts with NBC to be on the show, there may have been conflicts that did not allow Grimmie to sign with a competing record label: Universal Music Group vs Interscope Records (222 Records).  In the end, Grimmie signed on with Island Records where she released her new single "Must Be Love".
            a.icon(title='https://www.youtube.com/embed/XQHX5xhyzA0' href='') Must Be Love
            span.cd-date
          // cd-timeline-content
        // cd-timeline-block
        .cd-timeline-block
