            h2 The Beautiful Letdown
            img.croppedPhoto(src='../site/img/lyingpose.jpg' alt='lyingpose' align='right' style='width: 290px; height: auto')
            p.textwrap Christina's new single, "Must Be Love", received mixed reviews but were generally negative.  The song did not make full use of her incredible voice and it did not seem like Island Records were interested in backing up the singer by promoting the release.  There were also other issues surrounding her signing.  There have been reports that Grimmie was concerned with pressures from various mediums to "sexualize" her and have her appear for performances "half naked".  Due to her wholesome Christian values, Christina refused and stated her rejection of having to dress a certain way to sell records.  Whether this pressure was coming from Island Records directly is speculated.
            a(href='http://www.dailyrecord.co.uk/entertainment/celebrity/voice-usa-pop-sensation-christina-5269151#vKQrseg8CuVbFvW9.97') "...why she won't get undressed to impress"
            br
            a.icon(title='https://www.youtube.com/embed/AgFtEhmxw5I' href='') Photo Shoot at Island Records
            span.cd-date
