            h2 Dropped by Island -- Still Going Strong
            img.croppedPhoto(src='../site/img/cliche.png' alt='cliche' align='right' style='width: 250px; height: auto')
            p.textwrap After the release of the single "Must Be Love", on March 4, 2015, Island Records let Grimmie off the label so she can pursue other options freely.  The reasoning for the drop, stated by Grimmie, is that the label was being over burdened by other "big names" they had obligations to.  Despite this setback, Grimmie diligently started work on her new album and released her next single "Cliche" (Mar. 16 2015).  Following "Cliche", Grimmie worked on her next single, "Stay With Me"; a collaboration with Diamond Eyes.  "Stay With Me" was overall a hit and ranked five on the iTunes Electronic Charts.
            a.icon(title='https://www.youtube.com/embed/XQHX5xhyzA0' href='') Must Be Love
            br
            a.icon(title='https://www.youtube.com/embed/d9-S5DFEPeA' href='') Grimmie on Independence
