            h2 "Side A" EP
            img.croppedPhoto(src='../site/img/sideAcut.jpg' alt='sideA' align='right' style='width: 280px; height: auto')
            p.textwrap On February 21, 2016, Grimmie, independently again, released her 2nd EP, "Side A".  The EP was put together with four of her original songs: "Anybody's You", "Deception", "Without Him", and "Snow White".  Writing three of the four songs, the Side A EP was produced by Grimmie herself and the theme of the songs involved her own personal struggles she was dealing with.  In an interview with "PopCrush", Grimmie stated: "Side A was a project that I wanted to do, stuff that I produced completely and it was just stuff that I was dealing with. I haven’t had a lot of “hard times” in my life until recently, so I wanted to write about those things and get them out for my fans and not even worry about genre and just make music... Side A is supposed to be a project just from my heart and whatever is happening in my heart at the time". She also started touring with Rachel Platten on her Wildfire Tour from February to March, 2016, where she was able to perform song from her newly released album.
            a.icon(title='https://www.youtube.com/embed/gnjcEZZ0HZc' href='') Vlog about Side A
            br
